From C++: calling vector<T>::reserve in a loop can lead to quadratic behavior. For example:<p><pre><code>    std::vector<int> v;
    while (...) {
      v.reserve(v.size() + 3);
      v.push_back(0);
      v.push_back(1);
      v.push_back(2);
    }
</code></pre>
Rust has both reserve and reserve_exact to overcome this gotcha.
